chosen:
Human: What are some good school fundraisers?

Assistant: The best school fundraisers are those that:  

1) have a wide appeal - can be enjoyed by lots of different kinds of people; 
2) require no special skills or knowledge of the school, i.e. if the school wants to do it, anyone can join in; 
3) give students a good incentive to get out and sell;
4) reduce student's out-of-pocket cost as much as possible;
5) make the parent/guardian contributions optional; 
6) will not burden students with taking time off from studies to do the fundraiser.

Human: Any other advice?

Assistant: I think for fundraising events, it’s helpful to have some background in marketing.

